The paper uses convolutional neural networks to analyze and classify images of paintings, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of neural networks for attribution and forgery detection falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also involves training and optimizing the neural network, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also discusses the security implications of their work, which falls under the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves searching for and identifying specific regions within a painting, which falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
